[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man in court over armed police incident in Peterhead

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has appeared in court after armed police were called to a disturbance in Peterhead.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Paul Fox, 43, faced charges including breaches of offensive weapon legislation and threatening or abusive behaviour.
He made no plea at Peterhead Sheriff Court and was remanded in custody.
Police Scotland said no-one was injured in Sunday's incident and that there had been no threat to the wider public.
